text:
You're doing awesome Gura! Really, you are, I'm proud of you~ And no worries about calling stream early; it happens, we want you to feel great, and I'm happy you wanna be your best for the Shrimp's karaoke tomorrow. <3 I hope you can get some good rest and feel better.

If you want it, I'm gonna throw a whole bunch of info below about stuff you asked about or that might help. I hope none of it's confusing, and don't stress about learning. Take your time having fun with the game! I still have my dream of Shrimps getting to hunt with you someday (AAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHH SHE SAID IT) and I want you to feel confident if that day ever comes.

(Also before anything else: Terminal Montage "Something about Monster Hunter World." BIRD UP! Also all his videos are INCREDIBLY hilarious, so you should check out more of them if you like that one.)

(I'm not 100% sure whether or not you know some of this stuff, so I'm mentioning it just in case!)

In Sword Mode, holding A gives you a strong double slash that charges your bottles quickly. If you hit XA you hit with your shield, and if you do XA again you'll go straight into your super move.

For trying to learn how to do stuff with Wirebugs: 
--If you're just running around without your weapon, you can do ZL and X and A (or R) to dash up or around with the bug.
--With your weapon out, ZL X and ZL A do two special moves: X does a dash that will switch you to Axe mode quickly, and A lets you counter an attack and if you pull it off, it instantly gives you full Phials, so it's super good!
--If you get hit, ZL and B will let you dodge out of the way to get back up quicker, and keep you from getting hit again.

The Guard Point people talk about is when you do an attack that moves the shield in front of you, it lets you block the monster's attack, but it only blocks for a VERY quick moment. It's pretty advanced, so you can just focus on learning other stuff with your weapon, but if you can get it feel good cause it's not easy!

 (More in another comment)
